  "description": "Duo mode (voiceMode=2): the player's chord interval determines the synthesis character — a perfect fifth produces consonance, a tritone metallic chaos, a major third warm complexity. This is the core revelation of OUIE: your harmony choices are synthesis parameters. LFO1 sweeps HAMMER at 0.04 Hz — full cycles take 25 seconds, slow enough to be felt as tide rather than vibrato. breathRate=0.067 Hz (physiological ocean wave tempo). FM (voice 1, fmRatio=2.0) + Wavefolder (voice 2, algoParam=0.6): maximum STRIFE/LOVE contrast between feliX and Oscar algorithms. All four macros active. Coprime LFO rates at 0.04 and 0.067 Hz will not align for 25 seconds. The complete instrument, fully alive. Play two-note chords and let the tide carry you.",
