  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "The HAMMER is the instrument. The LFO is the tide. The interval is your voice.",
      "In Duo mode, the chord you choose is not just pitch — it is synthesis parameter. A fifth: consonance. A tritone: metallic chaos. Your harmony is the DSP.",
      "Hold two notes for 25 seconds. The HAMMER completes one full journey from STRIFE to LOVE and back. You will hear the engine's entire emotional range without touching a single control.",
      "This is what it means to design for journey, not destination."
    ],
    "revelation": "Nexus spoke: 'The Full Hammer is not a preset — it is a demonstration that the keyboard and the synthesis engine are the same instrument. In Duo mode, the player's interval choices travel the HAMMER's emotional range in real time. No other engine in the fleet makes harmony this structurally audible. The interval between two played notes determines FM ratios, ring modulation, and spectral blend simultaneously. This is the core revelation of OUIE.'",
    "god": "Nexus",
    "flock_note": "Play two-note chords exclusively. Begin with sustained fifths (C-G). After 10 seconds resolve to a third (E). After 10 more introduce a tritone (C-F#). Watch the HAMMER's 0.04 Hz sweep interact with your harmonic choices in real time — a conversation between your composition and the engine's autonomous evolution. This is OUIE played correctly.",
    "diagnosis": "The summit preset of Transcendental Vol 1. FM+Wavefolder provides the widest STRIFE/LOVE contrast of any feliX/Oscar pairing — FM's bright sidebands versus Wavefolder's folded harmonics create maximally distinct voices. Duo mode means every chord choice is heard through that contrast. LFO1 at 0.04 Hz is slow enough to be felt as environment rather than modulation. Coprime rates at 0.04 and 0.067 Hz will not align for approximately 25 seconds. All four macros are meaningfully active. This is the preset Guru Bin plays when asked what OUIE is."
  },
